From: Opsero <noreply@opsero.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm: xlnx: mixer: fix NULL deref + shutdown ordering in
 connector_init

When the xlnx_mixer driver is used in DRM-bridge mode (via the
xlnx_mixer.connect_drm_bridge=1 kernel cmdline param), the mixer's
.bind callback ends up calling xlnx_mix_connector_init() during
component_bind_all(), which runs synchronously from inside
xlnx_drm_pipeline_init() that is in turn called from xlnx_mix_probe().

xlnx_mix_connector_init() does:

	struct device *master_dev = &mixer->master->dev;
	encoder = devm_kzalloc(master_dev, sizeof(*encoder), GFP_KERNEL);

but mixer->master is assigned AFTER xlnx_drm_pipeline_init() returns:

	component_add(&pdev->dev, &xlnx_mix_component_ops);   /* triggers bind synchronously */
	...
	mixer->master = xlnx_drm_pipeline_init(pdev);          /* assigned after bind */

So mixer->master is NULL when the bind path runs, and dereferencing it
oopses on the first devm_kzalloc().

Naive fixes (using mixer->drm->dev with devm_kzalloc) introduce a
shutdown-time use-after-free: devres on the master platform device
unwinds during xlnx_unbind() before drm_managed_release() iterates the
mode-config objects, so DRM walks dangling encoder memory and oopses
inside drm_mode_config_cleanup().

This patch:

  1. Allocates the encoder via drmm_kzalloc(mixer->drm, ...) so the
     allocation is owned by the drm_device's drm_managed lifecycle.

  2. Replaces drm_simple_encoder_init() (which does NOT register a
     cleanup action) with drmm_encoder_init() — so a
     drm_encoder_cleanup() drm_managed action is registered AFTER the
     drmm_kzalloc release action. Because drm_managed runs cleanups in
     LIFO order, drm_encoder_cleanup() removes the encoder from
     mode_config.encoder_list BEFORE the memory is reaped, and BEFORE
     drm_mode_config_init_release() walks the (now-empty) list.

With both pieces in place, init succeeds (no NULL deref) and shutdown
ordering is correct (no use-after-free in drm_mode_config_cleanup ->
drm_encoder_cleanup -> drm_mode_object_unregister).

Signed-off-by: Opsero <noreply@opsero.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_mixer.c | 7 ++++---
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_mixer.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_mixer.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_mixer.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_mixer.c
@@ -20,6 +20,7 @@
 #include <drm/drm_gem_dma_helper.h>
 #include <drm/drm_framebuffer.h>
 #include <drm/drm_modeset_helper_vtables.h>
+#include <drm/drm_managed.h>
 #include <drm/drm_simple_kms_helper.h>
 #include <linux/clk.h>
 #include <linux/delay.h>
@@ -3212,16 +3213,15 @@ static int xlnx_mix_connector_init(struct xlnx_mix *mixer)
 {
 	struct drm_encoder *encoder;
 	struct drm_connector *connector;
-	struct device *master_dev = &mixer->master->dev;
 	int ret;

-	encoder = devm_kzalloc(master_dev, sizeof(*encoder), GFP_KERNEL);
+	encoder = drmm_kzalloc(mixer->drm, sizeof(*encoder), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (IS_ERR(encoder))
 		return PTR_ERR(encoder);

 	encoder->possible_crtcs |= drm_crtc_mask(&mixer->crtc.crtc);
-	ret = drm_simple_encoder_init(mixer->drm, encoder,
-				      DRM_MODE_ENCODER_NONE);
+	ret = drmm_encoder_init(mixer->drm, encoder, NULL,
+				DRM_MODE_ENCODER_NONE, NULL);
 	if (ret < 0)
 		return ret;

--
2.34.1
